title: For Trade:  BNIB Mossberg 715T .22 with 500 rds and a few more extras

This is a brand new, never fired tactical .22. Comes with one 25 magazine and magazine loader. Flat top receiver, 16.5 in barrel, front sling mount that rotates 180 degrees, and rail covers. Also comes with Magpul MOE forward grip, detachable iron sights, and 500 rds of ammo. 200 round nose, 200 hp, and 100 quiet rounds. The quiet rounds are powderless, and does not enough power to cycle the action. They do not jam the rifle, but you pretty much have to work it like a bolt action. However, they are about as loud as a BB gun, and I've been able to fire them in my back yard without any complaints from neighbors. 

The gun itself is pretty cool, and functions kinda like an AR. It has an ambidextrous magazine release, you can lock the bolt to the rear to make sure the chamber is empty, and the bolt catches when your magazine is empty, which is something most .22's do not do.

title: For Sale:  Gas Mask, Standard Issue M40A1, with carrier
postcontent:
I have a M40A1 gas mask in almost perfect condition. Size-large.  Item was worn to conduct sealing test before listing (which was a go), but has not been previously issued.

Can provide instructions on proper use during ftf if needed which is priceless.

FTF in central FL preferred, but will ship (US ONLY) at requested method using PayPal. $270 obo.

INCLUDED:
-M40A1 gas mask with drinking tube
-Unsealed cannister (1)
-Carrrier bag, 
-Second skin (black skin over front of mask)
-Tinted eye covers.  
-Manual / TM 3-4240-346-10
-Waterproof Chem/Bio Bag
*There is no quick-doff hood or other items


^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^*^
The M40 Field Protective mask features 3 voicemitters, one on either the right or left side, and one in front. A voicecom adapter may be placed over the front voicemitter to amplify the user's voice. The mask can be adjusted in the field to accept the filtering canister on either side, so that a weapon may be shouldered. Right-handed shooters will normally locate the canister on the left side of the mask and vice-versa.

The C2 canister on the M40 mask can protect the user from up to 15 nerve, choking, and blister agent attacks, and two blood agent attacks.

The M40 comes with a drinking system that allows the user to drink water when donning the mask for long periods of time in a chemically contaminated environment. In order to use the drinking system the user must also have suitably equipped canteen lids or an adapter for other containers.

The U.S. ARMY M40A1 Field Protective Gas Mask has been in use by the military of the United States since 1992 to protect from field concentrations of chemical and biological agents, along with radiological fallout particles. It still remains in U.S. Military service today.

The M40 series was reworked with a better nose cup and a new Butyl protective hood that covers the head and shoulder area. The new hood required a rubber "second skin" that covered the entire mask's face piece This new design offered a higher level of protection against penetrating NBC agents and also made it easier to don the protective hood.

--Canister with this item is opened, but again, was only used to conduct sealing test. It may be used as is, or replaced with other canisters.

Freedom Munitions "Like-New" manufacturing process provides like-new ammo performance.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS inspects all cartridge cases for defects. The Scharch Range Master machines are fully automated and cases are checked for any debris and pressure tested for any splits or cracks. Primers are removed, flash holes are cleared, and primer pockets are reamed to accept new primers.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS then washes cases in an acid wash specially designed to remove all remaining burnt powder from the flash hole and interior of the case which tumbling doesn't remove. Then cases are tumbled in a dryer for a factory look and finish.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS roll sizes all cases on our own designed machines to meet S.A.A.M.I.specification. This method is the industry standard for commercial sizing, insuring the case wall is sized down to the rim which insures new component performance.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS then loads these processed components on the same fiber optic-controlled Ammo Load machines as our premium new ammo. These are the same machines used by some of the largest manufacturers in the industry. These machines assure S.A.A.M.I. specifications for priming depth, pressure and overall cartridge length.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS "Like-New" manufacturing process with the new projectile, powder and primer assures factory ammo performance that discriminating shooters expect.

title: Want To Buy:  Looking to pay cash for permission to use private land to shoot on and possibly hunt wild problem hogs on...
location: Stuart, Palm City, Jupiter Farms, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent:
Hi, I am a 31yr old law abiding citizen & ccp holder with a passion for firearms & shooting. I reside in Palm City, FL.  Firearms safety, knowing my backdrop & where my bullet is going is a pet peeve of mine & I absolutely cannot stand being around people that are careless with firearms & do not respect them. 
 I wouldn't call myself a firearms "collector" but I am always looking to add to my firearm collection whenever financially possible.  

  I am NOT into bump-firing or anything trying to simulate full auto, I couldn't care any less about that kind of shooting.  I am into taking my time & being as accurate as I can be...doesn't matter if I'm shooting one of my many 22 rifles, an Ak, Sks or a 7mm mag bolt action...I treat them all the same. 
  I am not a fan of public ranges, don't like being around bunch of people...specially people that act like they don't have a clue what to do when their semi-auto ftf's, fte's, jams...etc...  plus I want to work on extending my shooting range past 200yds with a few of my rifles & I don't know of a range locally that has that capability.
    I am looking for someone that has property out in the country & would be willing to allow me the privilege to shoot on the property for a few hours a couple days per month.  It would always be on Saturday or Sunday as I work full time Mon-Fri. 

  I am willing to pay cash, preferably a one time lump sum payment per year.  I would be more than willing to hunt & do my part to rid your land of wild problem hogs if needed...and yes, I will hunt them for food, not just kill them for sport. If I have enough meat in the freezer, I will give it to someone who can use it.  

  You will Not have a problem with me bringing a bunch of people with me to shoot or hunt. I don't really have friends that are into shooting. I would like to be able bring my father with me sometimes as he enjoys shooting as well, although not to the same degree or as often as I do though. I would like to bring my wife with me occasionally, & my younger brother as well when he occasionally comes in to town. 
  I want to eventually buy some land out in the country to raise my growing family on & be able to shoot on but that is at least a few years down the road at minimum, So for now I am trying to find someone willing to allow me the privilege of the above mentioned proposition.  I would prefer the land be within 1hr or so of Stuart/Palm City.

title: For Sale:  Marlin No. 42 Pump Shotgun Exposed Hammer Takedown
postcontent:
This is a Marlin Pump Shotgun that is 12 Gauge. It is the takedown model, and being a no. 42 it is the last model of exposed hammer. This one has all of the safeties that Marlin added over the years (hammer, firing pin, slide position and inertia) My research shows that the 42 was made from 1922 to 1934. This has been completely disassembled, cleaned, inspected and reassembled. It is smooth. This model, like the 97 Winchester can be slam-fired by design. That means you can hold the trigger down, and when the action closes it will fire. The takedown process is a bit stiff, with the magazine tube being fairly tight in the receiver. The action is very smooth however and when I took it out it fed smoothly and functioned as expected. It has a Pachmayr White line recoil absorbing butt plate on it. 

$350 or would consider trades.
